    <section class="banner-carousel-card grid_wrapper grid_wrapper--large">
      <div class="heading-container">
                <h3>
          Challenges affecting Virunga-Bwindi-Volcanoes
        </h3>
              </div>
      <div class="splide">
        <div class="splide__track">
          <ul class="splide__list">
                                                                                                <li class="splide__slide" data-link-url="" data-link-text="Find out more">
                <figure>
                  <div class="caption-link-bg">
                    <figcaption>
                                                                                          <h4>Forest damage</h4>
                                            <p>The more people there are in an area, the less space for wildlife, and the more damage is often done to animals or their fragile environment. As well as wood and water, locals go into the forests to collect honey, pick medicinal plants or catch ‘bushmeat’.</p>
                    </figcaption>
                                      </div>
                </figure>
              </li>
                                                                                                <li class="splide__slide" data-link-url="" data-link-text="Find out more">
                <figure>
                  <div class="caption-link-bg">
                    <figcaption>
                                                                                          <h4>Livelihoods and wellbeing</h4>
                                            <p>We’ve been helping local people to realise the benefits (economic and environmental) of living alongside gorillas and other iconic wildlife, and of protecting the forests as an asset for themselves and future generations. And reducing their need to enter the forests by setting up rainwater harvesting tanks and supporting sustainable businesses such as bee-keeping.</p>
                    </figcaption>
                                      </div>
                </figure>
              </li>
                                                                                                <li class="splide__slide" data-link-url="" data-link-text="Find out more">
                <figure>
                  <div class="caption-link-bg">
                    <figcaption>
                                                                                          <h4>Tourism</h4>
                                            <p>We’re supporting sustainable eco-tourism initiatives, to help protect the landscape and mountain gorillas and benefit local communities. In addition to creating increased employment opportunities in the tourism sector, we’ve helped to introduce mechanisms, such as revenue sharing schemes, to ensure that local people benefit directly from this tourism. Profits from a range of sustainable tourism activities are ploughed back into the community via a diverse range of enterprises, helping to reduce poverty pressure and create financial incentives for conservation efforts</p>
                    </figcaption>
                                      </div>
                </figure>
              </li>
                                                                                                <li class="splide__slide" data-link-url="https://www.wwf.org.uk/what-we-do/preventing-human-wildlife-conflict" data-link-text="Learn more">
                <figure>
                  <div class="caption-link-bg">
                    <figcaption>
                                                                                          <h4>Human wildlife conflict</h4>
                                            <p>We’re supporting a range of methods to help reduce human-wildlife conflict. For example, we’ve helped local people to establish tea plantations to create a ‘buffer zone’ between some areas of mountain gorilla habitat and human settlement. Tea isn’t palatable to gorillas, so they are less tempted to wander onto agricultural land searching for food. We also work with community patrols who can chase mountain gorillas and other wildlife back into the forest if they stray onto people’s land whilst also collecting important monitoring data to inform future management of conflict.</p>
                    </figcaption>
                                          <div class="btn-wrap">
                        <div class="btn-wrap--item">
                          <a href="https://www.wwf.org.uk/what-we-do/preventing-human-wildlife-conflict" class="btn btn--white">
                            Learn more
                          </a>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                                      </div>
                </figure>
              </li>
                                                                                                <li class="splide__slide" data-link-url="https://www.wwf.org.uk/learn/wildlife/mountain-gorillas" data-link-text="More about gorillas">
                <figure>
                  <div class="caption-link-bg">
                    <figcaption>
                                                                                          <h4>Monitoring mountain gorillas</h4>
                                            <p>We’re working to strengthen community and ranger based monitoring of mountain gorillas, their habitats, and the associated threats. We also help to carry out census surveys of the remaining mountain gorilla populations. All of which helps to ensure that management and policy decisions are based on good quality scientific data.</p>
                    </figcaption>
                                          <div class="btn-wrap">
                        <div class="btn-wrap--item">
                          <a href="https://www.wwf.org.uk/learn/wildlife/mountain-gorillas" class="btn btn--white">
                            More about gorillas
                          </a>
                        </div>
                      </div>
                                      </div>
                </figure>
              </li>
                                                                                                <li class="splide__slide" data-link-url="" data-link-text="Find out more">
                <figure>
                  <div class="caption-link-bg">
                    <figcaption>
                                                                                          <h4>Oil, gas and mineral extraction</h4>
                                            <p>There have been various proposals to search for oil in and around Virunga National Park, which we believe presents an unacceptable risk for the environment, people and wildlife here.</p>
                    </figcaption>
                                      </div>
                </figure>
              </li>
                      </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="cta-pagination-container">
          <div class="splide-arrows-bg">
            <div class="splide__arrows splide__arrows--ltr">
              <button
                class="splide__arrow splide__arrow--prev"
